content:
<@!689161464829050960> <@!543900561460822016> 
What is the reason behind using an auto generator for rendering files in `eth1.0-specs`? 
A few problem/concerns that I have:
- IIUC, our ultimate goal is to merge this into the `eth2.0-specs` repo . In `eth2.0-specs` repo markdown is manually written by the dev. This will cause compatibility  problems for formatting.
- There's no way I can organise the content in a meaningful way. I can't write table of contents in a nested way . 
- Whenever I desire to add custom formatting it's not possible. eg. I don't know how to add description for Constants declared in a file. eg. https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/weak-subjectivity.md#custom-types

author: lightclient
content: I think we prefer to generate the documentation from the code rather than the reverse (the way the eth2 specs does it). Formatting will be a bit more challenging than with the eth2 specs repo, but i expect everything else will be more pleasant (e.g. don't need to also maintain a markdown->python transpiler).

author: samwilsn
content:
From my somewhat limited understanding of sphinx, we get complete control over the generated documentation. If we want to go 100% manual, we can hand write every line of the docs in reStructuredText if we want to.

I've chosen to go with autoapi for this first pass,because, like <@!543900561460822016> has said, we want to prioritize getting a complete specification without bikeshedding too much on the documentation itself. The downside to autoapi is that we lose some control over the autogenerated pages.

author: samwilsn
content:
That said, there are quite a few upsides to using sphinx+autoapi, like:

 - Auto-linking to types and functions.
 - Uniform look and feel.
 - Less chance of documentation getting out-of-sync with the code.
 - Uses traditional python tooling instead of custom markdown linkers.

author: samwilsn
content: I have a fairly strong preference for autogenerating the documentation from the code, but I'm open to being convinced otherwise ðŸ˜„

author: samwilsn
content: My biggest complaint so far is that reStructuredText is _really_ foreign.
